Spec: Signature Verifier Service
Purpose:
  Verify a downloaded SpecDD distribution zip against its detached OpenPGP signature using bundled trusted project keys.

Structure:
  ./signature-verifier.ts: Signature verifier service implementation.
  ./trusted-keys.ts: Trusted release signing key metadata and armored public key strings.
  ./signature-verifier.test.ts: Signature verifier tests.

Owns:
  ./signature-verifier.ts
  ./trusted-keys.ts
  ./signature-verifier.test.ts

References:
  /src/infrastructure/file-system.sdd
  ../logger/logger.sdd

Must:
  Accept @Logger and @FileSystem through constructor parameters.
  Accept a path to a distribution .zip file and a path to its matching .zip.asc detached signature file.
  Read the zip and detached signature through @FileSystem.
  Verify the detached signature against the exact zip file bytes.
  Load public release signing keys embedded in ./trusted-keys.ts as armored OpenPGP string constants.
  Pin trusted signing keys by full OpenPGP fingerprint.
  Accept signatures only from fingerprints listed in @TRUSTED_RELEASE_SIGNING_KEYS.
  Support release signing key rotation by allowing more than one trusted fingerprint.
  Return the verified signer fingerprint and validated file paths.

Must not:
  Execute gpg or any other external command.
  Fetch public keys from the network.
  Trust public keys downloaded with the release being verified.
  Accept signatures from unknown fingerprints.
  Modify the provided zip or signature files.

Depends on:
  @CliError
  @Logger
  @FileSystem
  openpgp
  @CODE_SIGNING_2026_01_PUBLIC_KEY
  @TRUSTED_RELEASE_SIGNING_KEYS

Exposes:
  @SignatureVerifier
  @SignatureVerifier.verifyDistribution
  @TrustedReleaseSigningKey
  @CODE_SIGNING_2026_01_PUBLIC_KEY
  @TRUSTED_RELEASE_SIGNING_KEYS

Accepts:
  @SignatureVerificationRequest

Returns:
  @SignatureVerificationResult

Raises:
  @SignatureInputNotFoundError
  @SignaturePublicKeyLoadError
  @SignatureUnknownSignerError
  @SignatureInvalidError
  @SignatureVerificationError

Handles:
  valid detached signature
  invalid detached signature
  missing zip file
  missing signature file
  malformed signature file
  malformed bundled public key
  signature made by an untrusted key
